   "source": [
    "# Notebook 1 — AWS Account & GPU Instance Setup\n",
    "**MAI 656 — Natural Language Processing | Canadian University Dubai | Spring 2026**\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook walks you through the **one-time AWS account setup** and launching a GPU instance for the Arabic Handwritten Text Recognition project.\n",
    "\n",
    "> ⚠️ **This notebook contains no runnable code — all steps are performed in the AWS Console and your local terminal.**\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Quick Reference\n",
    "\n",
    "| Item | Value |\n",
    "|------|-------|\n",
    "| AWS Instance | g5.xlarge (NVIDIA A10G, 24 GB VRAM) |\n",
    "| AMI | Deep Learning OSS PyTorch Ubuntu 22 |\n",
    "| Region | us-east-1 (cheapest for GPU) |\n",
    "| Storage | 100 GB gp3 |\n",
    "| Cost | ~$1.00/hr on-demand |\n",
    "| Training time | ~2–4 hours |\n",
    "| Total cost per run | ~$3–5 |\n",
    "\n",
    "> 🚨 **Always terminate your instance when done. A running g5.xlarge costs ~$24/day.**"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 1 — Create an AWS Account\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Go to https://aws.amazon.com and create an account.\n",
    "2. You will need a credit card (you are only charged for what you use).\n",
    "3. New accounts get some free-tier credits, but **GPU instances are NOT free-tier**."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 2 — Request GPU Quota\n",
    "\n",
    "By default, new AWS accounts have **zero GPU quota**. You must request it:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Go to **Service Quotas → Amazon EC2**\n",
    "2. Search for: **Running On-Demand G and VT instances**\n",
    "3. Click **Request quota increase**\n",
    "4. Request a value of **4** (g5.xlarge needs 4 vCPUs)\n",
    "5. Wait for approval — usually 1–24 hours\n",
    "\n",
    "> ⚠️ Without this step you will get an error when launching your instance."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 3 — Create a Key Pair\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Go to **EC2 → Key Pairs → Create key pair**\n",
    "2. Name: `nlp-project`\n",
    "3. Key type: RSA | Format: `.pem`\n",
    "4. Download and save the file — **do not lose it**\n",
    "5. In your local terminal, set permissions:\n",
    "\n",
    "```bash\n",
    "chmod 400 ~/Downloads/nlp-project.pem\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 4 — Create a Security Group\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Go to **EC2 → Security Groups → Create security group**\n",
    "2. Name: `nlp-gpu-server`\n",
    "3. Add inbound rules:\n",
    "   - SSH (port 22) — your IP only\n",
    "   - Custom TCP (port 8000) — your IP only (for the inference server)\n",
    "4. Save"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 5 — Launch the GPU Instance\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Go to **EC2 → Launch Instance**\n",
    "2. Configure as follows:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Setting | Value |\n",
    "|---------|-------|\n",
    "| Name | nlp-finetuning |\n",
    "| AMI | Search "Deep Learning OSS Nvidia Driver AMI GPU PyTorch" → choose Ubuntu 22.04 |\n",
    "| Instance type | g5.xlarge |\n",
    "| Key pair | nlp-project |\n",
    "| Security group | nlp-gpu-server |\n",
    "| Storage | 100 GB, type gp3 |\n",
    "\n",
    "3. Click **Launch instance**\n",
    "4. Note the **Instance ID** — you will need it to terminate later"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 6 — Connect via SSH & Verify GPU\n",
    "\n",
    "Wait ~2 minutes for the instance to boot, then in your **local terminal**:\n",
    "\n",
    "```bash\n",
    "# Replace <PUBLIC_IP> with your instance's public IP from the EC2 console\n",
    "ssh -i ~/Downloads/nlp-project.pem ubuntu@<PUBLIC_IP>\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "Once connected, verify the GPU:\n",
    "\n",
    "```bash\n",
    "nvidia-smi\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "Expected output: `NVIDIA A10G | 24 GB VRAM`.\n",
    "\n",
    "If you see an error, the AMI may need a reboot:\n",
    "\n",
    "```bash\n",
    "sudo reboot\n",
    "# Wait 1 minute, then SSH again\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 7 — Set Up the Environment on the Instance\n",
    "\n",
    "Run these commands on the **GPU instance** (after SSH):\n",
    "\n",
    "```bash\n",
    "# Create and activate a conda environment\n",
    "conda create -n nlp python=3.11 -y\n",
    "conda activate nlp\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create project directories\n",
    "mkdir -p ~/project\n",
    "cd ~/project\n",
    "mkdir -p data/raw data/processed data/train data/eval\n",
    "mkdir -p models/lora_adapter\n",
    "mkdir -p logs\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "### Upload your code\n",
    "\n",
    "**Option A — SCP from local machine:**\n",
    "```bash\n",
    "scp -i ~/Downloads/nlp-project.pem -r ./your_code/* ubuntu@<PUBLIC_IP>:~/project/\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "**Option B — Clone from GitHub:**\n",
    "```bash\n",
    "cd ~/project\n",
    "git clone https://github.com/YOUR_REPO.git .\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "### Install dependencies\n",
    "```bash\n",
    "pip install -r requirements.txt\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 8 — Terminate Your Instance When Done\n",
    "\n",
    "> 🚨 **This is the most important step. A forgotten g5.xlarge costs ~$24/day (~$720/month).**\n",
    "\n",
    "**Option A — AWS Console:** EC2 → Instances → select instance → Actions → Instance State → Terminate\n",
    "\n",
    "**Option B — CLI:**\n",
    "```bash\n",
    "aws ec2 terminate-instances --instance-ids i-YOUR_INSTANCE_ID --region us-east-1\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "**Option C — Stop (preserves data, still charges for storage):**\n",
    "```bash\n",
    "aws ec2 stop-instances --instance-ids i-YOUR_INSTANCE_ID --region us-east-1\n",
    "# ~$0.08/GB/month = ~$8/month for 100 GB\n",
    "\n",
    "# Restart later:\n",
    "aws ec2 start-instances --instance-ids i-YOUR_INSTANCE_ID --region us-east-1\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Troubleshooting Cheat Sheet\n",
    "\n",
    "| Problem | Cause | Fix |\n",
    "|---------|-------|-----|\n",
    "| InsufficientInstanceCapacity | No GPU available in AZ | Try a different AZ or region |\n",
    "| vCPU quota exceeded | Old instance still shutting down | Wait 5 min, then try again |\n",
    "| AccessDeniedException | Missing IAM permissions | Check IAM policy has EC2 access |\n",
    "| `python: command not found` | AMI uses python3 | Always use `python3` |\n",
    "| GPU not visible after boot | AMI needs first-boot init | Run `sudo reboot`, wait 1 min, reconnect |"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
